  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The primary objective is to establish if the SternumFix System improves sternal closure. The
      study should test the hypothesis that in a high risk patient population with increased risk
      for the development of sternal wound complications SternumFix will reduce the incidence of
      sternal healing complications. The control group will be treated with wire cerclage, the
      standard method of sternal closure.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
